name: Caterpie
flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokemon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Metapod
flavorText: Its shell is filled with its soft innards. It doesn't move much because of the risk it might carelessly spill its innards out.
Attack2Text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Butterfree
flavorText: Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.
Attack1Text: Heal all damage from all of your Pokemon. Shuffle this Pokemon and all cards attached to it into your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Oddish
flavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Gloom
flavorText: Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Vileplume
flavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, your opponent's Basic Pokemon can't attack.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Tangela
flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Tangrowth
flavorText: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Ledyba
flavorText: They are timid and grow uneasy when not in a swarm with others of their kind. The pattern on their backs differs slightly from one to another.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Ledian
flavorText: While it's believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pokemon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, or any other effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Heracross
flavorText: This powerful Pokemon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies' bellies, then lifts and throws them.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokemon is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Pansage
flavorText: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokemon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

name: Simisage
flavorText: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokemon is wild tempered.
Attack2Text: You may attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Dewpider
flavorText: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Araquanid
flavorText: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokemon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.
Attack1Text: Energy can't be attached to the Defending Pokemon from your opponent's hand during their next turn.

name: Wimpod
flavorText: This Pokemon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.
Ability1Text: During your first turn, this Pokemon has no Retreat Cost.

name: Golisopod-GX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokemon this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Charmander
flavorText: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander's life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.

name: Charmander
flavorText: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander's life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.

name: Charizard-GX
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Fire Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Ho-Oh-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Phoenix Burn during your next turn.

name: Pansear
flavorText: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.

name: Simisear
flavorText: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.
Attack2Text: Attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Heatmor
flavorText: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, put a card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Salazzle-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Prize card you have taken.

name: Turtonator
flavorText: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.
Attack1Text: Attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Alolan Vulpix
flavorText: It exhales air colder than -58 degrees Fahrenheit. Elderly people in Alola call this Pokemon by an older name—Keokeo.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Alolan Ninetales
flavorText: It creates drops of ice in its coat and showers them over its enemies. Anyone who angers it will be frozen stiff in an instant.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon by your opponent's Pokemon-GX or Pokemon-EX.

name: Horsea
flavorText: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Seadra
flavorText: Its body bristles with sharp spikes. Carelessly trying to touch it could cause fainting from the spikes.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kingdra
flavorText: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.
Attack1Text: This attack does 90 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Discard a Water Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Magikarp
flavorText: Although weak and helpless, this Pokemon is incredibly fertile. They exist in such multitudes, you'll soon grow tired of seeing them.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: A tale is told of a town that angered Gyarados. Before the sun rose the next day, flames utterly consumed the town, leaving not a trace behind.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Magikarp in your discard pile.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Marill
flavorText: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry, even when it plays in the water.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Azumarill
flavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from the attacks of your opponent's Fire or Water Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Panpour
flavorText: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.

name: Simipour
flavorText: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.
Attack2Text: Move a Water Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Bruxish
flavorText: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that shares a type with your opponent's Active Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Tapu Fini-GX
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Water Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Tapu Fini-GX
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Water Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Pikachu
flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Raichu
flavorText: It unleashes electric shocks that can reach 100,000 volts. When agitated, it can knock out even an Indian elephant.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may leave your opponent's Active Pokemon Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: Half of all sudden blackouts are caused by Electabuzz gathering at electric power plants and gobbling up electricity.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Electivire
flavorText: It pushes the tips of its tails against its foes and then lets loose a high-voltage current. Its foes are burned to a crisp in an instant.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage. If tails, this Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon has any Water Energy attached to it, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon's maximum HP is 100 or more, this attack does nothing.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: You may do 80 more damage. If you do, this attack does 80 damage to 1 of your Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Togedemaru
flavorText: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokemon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Slowking
flavorText: A poisonous bite reacted with its system, blessing it with the enhanced intellect of a genius. It has full control of its psychic powers.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If you have no cards in your hand, ignore all Energy in this attack's cost.

name: Wobbuffet
flavorText: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to build up its counterstrike.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Seviper
flavorText: In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.
Ability1Text: Put 1 more damage counter on your opponent's Poisoned Pokemon between turns.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Duskull
flavorText: It doggedly pursues its prey wherever it goes. However, the chase is abandoned at sunrise.
Attack1Text: Put a Basic Pokemon from your discard pile onto your Bench.

name: Dusclops
flavorText: Anyone who dares peer into its body to see its spectral ball of fire will have their spirit stolen away.
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on each Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Dusknoir
flavorText: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent reveal their hand. Put a Basic Pokemon you find there onto your opponent's Bench, and put 3 damage counters on that Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Croagunk
flavorText: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Toxicroak
flavorText: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 80 more damage. Then, remove that Special Condition from this Pokemon.

name: Venipede
flavorText: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Whirlipede
flavorText: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Scolipede
flavorText: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Espurr
flavorText: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon's Weakness is now Psychic until the end of your next turn. (The amount of Weakness doesn't change.)

name: Meowstic
flavorText: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck to dust.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage for each card in your hand.

name: Sandygast
flavorText: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokemon embodies the grudges of the departed.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Palossand
flavorText: Possessed people controlled by this Pokemon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Discard all cards from both Active Pokemon.

name: Necrozma-GX
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Colorless Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Discard all Psychic Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 60 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: This attack does 100 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon-GX and Pokemon-EX. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Machamp-GX
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is an Evolution Pokemon, this attack does 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard any Stadium card in play.

name: Rhyhorn
flavorText: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokemon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.

name: Rhydon
flavorText: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Rhyperior
flavorText: From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Lunatone
flavorText: Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.
Ability1Text: If you have Solrock in play, Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's) can't be healed.

name: Solrock
flavorText: Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It can discern the physical and emotional states of people, Pokemon, and other natural things from the shape of their aura waves.

name: Lucario
flavorText: Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon until the end of your opponent's next turn.

name: Sawk
flavorText: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.
Attack1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Basic Pokemon during your opponent's next turn. This Pokemon can't use Quick Guard during your next turn.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance or any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Crabrawler
flavorText: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

name: Crabominable
flavorText: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokemon evolved and grew fur.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself for each damage counter on it.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: The more intimidating the opponent it faces, the more this Pokemon's blood boils. It will attack with no regard for its own safety.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.

name: Mudbray
flavorText: The mud stuck to Mudbray's hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Mudsdale
flavorText: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 30 damage to itself. This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Passimian
flavorText: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.
Attack2Text: Discard a Pokemon Tool card from your hand. If you don't, this attack does nothing.

name: Marshadow-GX
Ability1Text: This Pokemon can use the attacks of any Basic Pokemon in your discard pile. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage times the amount of basic Energy attached to this Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Alolan Rattata
flavorText: With its incisors, it gnaws through doors and infiltrates people's homes. Then, with a twitch of its whiskers, it steals whatever food it finds.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Bite attack's base damage is 60.

name: Alolan Raticate
flavorText: It forms a group of Rattata, which it assumes command of. Each group has its own territory, and disputes over food happen often.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Alolan Grimer
flavorText: A Grimer, which had been brought in to solve a problem with garbage, developed over time into this form.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for Alolan Grimer and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Alolan Muk-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 70 more damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Sneasel
flavorText: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Slash attack's base damage is 80.

name: Weavile
flavorText: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to each Pokemon that has an Ability (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Darkrai
flavorText: It chases people and Pokemon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has already used their GX attack, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Darkrai-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. Then, attach a Darkness Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, that Pokemon is Knocked Out. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Darkrai-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. Then, attach a Darkness Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, that Pokemon is Knocked Out. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Inkay
flavorText: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Malamar
flavorText: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokemon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: You may move all Energy attached to this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Ralts
flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokemon, its body warms up slightly.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.

name: Gardevoir-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Fairy Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage times the amount of Energy attached to both Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Shuffle 10 cards from your discard pile into your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Diancie
flavorText: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Pokemon and put it onto that Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Fairy Pokemon.

name: Cutiefly
flavorText: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it's able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

name: Ribombee
flavorText: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Morelull
flavorText: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

name: Shiinotic
flavorText: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon 30 damage times the amount of Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Noivern-GX
Attack1Text: Your opponent can't play any Item cards from their hand during their next turn.
Attack2Text: Your opponent can't play any Special Energy cards from their hand during their next turn.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: This is Zygarde's form at times when it uses its overwhelming power to suppress those who endanger the ecosystem.
Attack2Text: Discard a Darkness Energy and a Fairy Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Meowth
flavorText: It lies around all day, becoming active near dusk. At night, it wanders the city in search of loose change.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Persian
flavorText: It has a violent temperament. It will attack anything that looks it in the eye. Its sharp claws inflict deep wounds.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, the Defending Pokemon takes 60 more damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Porygon
flavorText: Roughly 20 years ago, it was artificially created, utilizing the latest technology of the time.
Attack1Text: Look at 1 of your opponent's face-down Prize cards.

name: Porygon2
flavorText: For the purposes of planetary development, Porygon was updated with the most cutting-edge technology available.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 6 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

name: Porygon-Z
flavorText: In order to create a more advanced Pokemon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may devolve each of your opponent's evolved Pokemon by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't use Zap Cannon during your next turn.

name: Porygon-Z
flavorText: In order to create a more advanced Pokemon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may devolve each of your opponent's evolved Pokemon by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't use Zap Cannon during your next turn.

name: Hoothoot
flavorText: It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

name: Noctowl
flavorText: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Discard a Pokemon from it.

name: Bouffalant
flavorText: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: You may discard any Stadium card in play.

name: Noibat
flavorText: They live in pitch black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Stufful
flavorText: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Bewear
flavorText: This immensely dangerous Pokemon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Golisopod-GX
